The paper discusses spreadsheet engineering methodologies, which involves software engineering principles applied to spreadsheets. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the organization and interpretation of spreadsheet engineering recommendations, which involves programming languages and paradigms, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also considers resource constraints and development parameters, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper mentions the need for further research, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases).
